Looking to sell this .357 Magnum S&W Model M&P 340. It's one of the ones they've made in recent years without the internal lock. It's in excellent condition, as it's never been fired and has just been sitting in a nightstand safe since I bought it new earlier this year. These are awesome CC guns. It weighs in at about 13.3oz! The frame is a Scandium/Aluminum alloy and the barrel & cylinder are both stainless steel for added durability. It's also got a U-notch rear site with a Tritium Big Dot front site (all factory-original).

The gun would include everything it came with new, box/papers/fired casing/etc. It took me a while to track this down and I can see that I'll have a hard time finding another one, as S&W only made a couple runs of these no-lock guns and they don't appear to be starting another run anytime soon (if ever?!)...a bit hard to come by, especially unfired. I know I'll probably regret selling it, but another S&W has caught my attention and I haven't even fired this one...so I figured I'll pass it on.

Thanks for looking and please feel free to ask any questions.

title: For Sale:  Slide Fire SSAR-15 SBS Bump-Fire Stock AR-15
postcontent:
Slide Fire SSAR-15 SBS (Standard Battle Stock) Bump-Fire Stock AR-15

The Slide Fire Solutions SSAR-15 SBS (Standard Battle Stock) Bump Fire Buttstock is the latest iteration of the company's groundbreaking SSAR-15 OGR Original Bump Fire Stock, incorporating the same performance, reliability, and superior craftsmanship of the OGR with a new look designed to appear similar to many of today's popular, modern battle rifle stocks. The SSAR-15 SBS allows the shooter to safely bump fire their AR-15 from the shoulder, effectively and legally simulating fully automatic fire, and allowing for an unprecedented measure of control that is severely lacking when attempting to bump fire a rifle in the traditional, "from-the-hip" manner. 

The SSAR-15 features a shelf that positions the shooter's index finger in a fixed position in front of the rifle's trigger. To fire, the upper receiver is moved forward with the support hand pushing on the forend, thereby bringing the trigger to the shooter's finger and discharging a round. The rifle's recoil causes the upper receiver to move rearward, allowing the trigger mechanism to reset. When the right amount of constant forward pressure is applied, the rifle will continue to fire as the trigger is brought forward and depressed by the shooter's stationary index finger, causing the gun to Bump Fire. With a little practice, the shooter will be capable of delivering accurate single shots, bursts, or even full magazine dumps on demand using the SSAR-15. 

The SSAR-15 is designed for installation onto any Mil-Spec Diameter AR-15 Collapsible Stock Receiver Extension Buffer Tube. Installation involves removing the factory pistol grip, replacing it with the included Interface Block, and sliding the SSAR-15 onto the buffer tube. No permanent modifications or gunsmithing required! Each SSAR-15 assembly includes the SBS Buttstock, an Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions, BATFE Approval Letter and Lifetime Factory Warranty. Made in the USA. 

Technical Information:

Model: SSAR-15 SBS Right Hand

Stock Material: Reinforced High Strength Polymer

Length of Pull: 13"

Compatibility: AR-15 with Mil-Spec Diameter Collapsible Stock Buffer Tube

Includes: SSAR-15 SBS Stock, Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions, BATFE Approval Letter

Some aftermarket sling adapter receiver end plates are NOT compatible with this stock

SSAR-15 Stocks are compatible with most enlarged winter trigger guards

Sig Sauer P 229 in 357 SIG DAK Night Sights

This is a used Sig Sauer P229 in excellent condition chambered in 357 SIG with 3.9” barrel, 12 round magazine, night sights, tactical rail, stainless steel slide and aluminum alloy frame with Nitron finish WITH THE DAK SYSTEM. IT comes in a Sig Sauer factory padded hard case and trigger lock

SIG recently released an improved version of the double-action only (DAO) pistols; this version is called the DAK (for Double Action Kellerman, after the designer of the system). The DAK capability is available in 226, 229 and 239 models. When firing the pistol the first trigger pull is only 6.5 lbf (compared to 10 pounds for the standard DAO). After the pistol fires and the trigger is released forward the trigger has an intermediate reset point that is approximately halfway to the trigger at rest position. The trigger pull from this intermediate reset point is 8.5 lbf. If the trigger is released all the way forward, this will engage the primary trigger reset and have a trigger pull of 6.5 lbf. To engage the intermediate reset, the trigger must be held to the rear while the slide is cycled, either manually or by the recoil of a round being fired. The United States Coast Guard has adopted this firearm as its PDW (Personal Defense Weapon), replacing the older M9 pistol.[5]
